        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 3:07PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 307 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southwest of Deadmans Basin Reservoir, or 19 miles southeast
of Harlowton, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ryegate.

The strongest portion of this storm is expected to track south of
Highway 12.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
